#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Bad news for those waiting to be mask free from Thursday. The Health Department says it is still compulsory to wear a mask in enclosed indoor spaces except for children in schools. READ: COVID-19 restrictions to lapse at midnight The department has extended the public consultation period for health regulation amendments until 5 July. In the interim, travellers arriving in South Africa will still have to produce a valid vaccination certificate or a negative PCR test. Outdoor venues can still only use 50 percent of their capacity with attendees needing to show proof of vaccination.